Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @baking potato{1} and @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them both onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

== Chive Dressing ==

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Finely chop the @chives{1} (use #scissors{} if easier).

> TIP: Discard any tough stalks from the cavolo nero at this stage.

== Salmon and Dressing ==

Drizzle the @salmon fillets{2} with the @olive oil{for the marinade}. Season with @salt{} and half the @Cajun spice mix{1}. Rub onto both sides of the fish.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

In a small #bowl{}, mix the remaining Cajun spice mix with half the chives, a pinch of lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and the @olive oil{for the dressing}. Season with @salt{} and set your chive dressing to one side.

== Cavolo Nero Mash ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @cavolo nero{100%g}(chopped) and a splash of water and cover until wilted, ~{3-4%mins}.

Remove the lid, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%min} more.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Salmon ==

Wipe out your (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, carefully place your salmon into the pan, skin-side down.

Cook for ~{3-4%mins} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%mins} on the other side.

> TIP: To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking skin-side down.
> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Assembly ==

When the potatoes are cooked, add them to your bowl of cavolo nero and roughly mash with a #potato masher{}. Mix in a knob of @?butter{} and the remaining chives. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Serve your cavolo nero mash topped with the spiced fish and a drizzle of chive dressing.

Chop any remaining lemon into wedges and serve alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!